<i>Posted by Melyodas on 03-22-2004 06:45 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Not sure if this helps or not, but I wrote SOE about this the other day about the $99 deal and upgrading to the "all in one" deal once EQ2 comes out and this is what they had to say:<br />
<br />
> Hello,<br />
> <br />
> Thank you for contacting the Sony Online Entertainment Customer Service <br />
> department.<br />
> <br />
> "If I bought the full year now, what happens when EQ2 comes out?  Will I<br />
> be able to upgrade to the all in one or some other combination plan even<br />
> though I haven't used my full year?"<br />
> <br />
> Your EverQuest account will be prorated for the adjustment.  Remember <br />
> that all paid amounts are prepaid.  You will not lose any time.<br />
<br />
The word "prorated" made me perk up a bit, as I thought they never gave any kind of reimbursement for anything....Wrote back to confirm this and I havent heard back.  I want to know exactly WHAT they are prorating and HOW.<br />
<br />
I'm guessing the guy is probably on the rack or in the iron maiden right now.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
